<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-24T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="832" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d832">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.516/110</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-24T14:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1915, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your December 22, 6 p.m., relative bank situation. Parker being
                            instructed to repeat to you lengthy telegram on this matter. Immediately
                            upon its receipt lay matter before Carranza and urgently request, in
                            view of the serious consequences that may result from the <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> Government’s attitude in this matter,
                            that the banks be given sufficient time to meet the requirements of the
                            order.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>